CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 15, 1946, pg. 16, reads: "Brilliant Young Artist at Work - Sterling Curry, 19-year-old son of Mrs. Lorraine Curry of Henderson Street, works on a drawing entitled 'Do Unto Others.'  Sterling won three awards in the national contest sponsored recently by the American Time Corporation and some of his paintings were on exhibit at Carnegie Museum on May 6 through June 6. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Artist Sterling Curry working on his drawing "Do Unto Others"
